The  Aditya Birla Group  plans to
invest $1 billion in the next five years to develop solar power
projects in India, the Economic Times newspaper reported citing
Dev Bhattacharya, head of strategy.  The group, which runs businesses from cement to
telecommunications, has so far invested 2 billion rupees ($39
million) to develop 20 megawatts of solar capacity and targets
having 100 megawatts in 18 months, according to the report.  Aditya Birla Group acquired a minority stake in a
photovoltaic plant in Gujarat state controlled by  Electrotherm
India Ltd. (ELT) , according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
